<subSubSection id="52956573CC08C12CFF7EFA69FEE1F967" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1A3036F8CC08C12CFF7EFA69FEE1F967" blockId="10.[151,1437,1332,1784]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFF7EFA69FECCFA7F" bold="true" box="[197,324,1410,1436]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
It is useful to compare the genitalia of the 
<typeStatus id="C534885ACC08C12CFC87FA69FCE6FA7F" box="[828,878,1410,1436]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFC2DFA68FB8DFA7F" box="[918,1029,1411,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFC2DFA68FB8DFA7F" box="[918,1029,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">crenulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with those of the 
<typeStatus id="C534885ACC08C12CFB62FA69FA83FA7F" box="[1241,1291,1410,1436]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFA88FA68FA1CFA7F" box="[1331,1428,1411,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFA88FA68FA1CFA7F" box="[1331,1428,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both species being included by 
<bibRefCitation id="7E1E4B09CC08C12CFD99FA42FCBCFA20" author="Hampson" box="[546,820,1449,1475]" pageId="10" pageNumber="52" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1900) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. Arctiadae (Nolinae, Lithosianae). Vol. II. Trustees of the British Museum, London, XX + 589 pp." type="book" year="1900">
Hampson (
<number id="AC4724DFCC08C12CFD11FA42FD66FA20" box="[682,750,1449,1475]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="1900.0">1900</number>
: 
<number id="AC4724DFCC08C12CFD40FA42FCA3FA20" box="[763,811,1449,1475]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="447.0">447</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
among the synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFBD4FA42FB62FA21" box="[1135,1258,1449,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliterata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFBD4FA42FB62FA21" box="[1135,1258,1449,1474]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">obliterata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Compared to 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFF2CFA3BFF71FA0A" box="[151,249,1488,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFF2CFA3BFF71FA0A" box="[151,249,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the saccus is more rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFDDDFA3BFD5DFA0A" box="[614,725,1488,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFDDDFA3BFD5DFA0A" box="[614,725,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">crenulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the distal portion of ala valvae is longer than the supravalva in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFF0EFA1CFE9EF9F3" box="[181,278,1527,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFF0EFA1CFE9EF9F3" box="[181,278,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the distal portion of the supravalva is larger in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFCF0FA1CFC32F9F3" box="[843,954,1527,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFCF0FA1CFC32F9F3" box="[843,954,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">crenulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the costa of the supravalva is straight in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFF2CF9F6FE80F9D5" box="[151,264,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFF2CF9F6FE80F9D5" box="[151,264,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">crenulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(undulated in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFE0CF9F6FD92F9D5" box="[439,538,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFE0CF9F6FD92F9D5" box="[439,538,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the vesica has a cornutus longer than three fifth of the total length of the aedeagus in both species, but is stronger and conical in 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFC9EF9AFFC1CF9BE" box="[805,916,1604,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFC9EF9AFFC1CF9BE" box="[805,916,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">crenulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The wing venation has not been examined. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="52956573CC08C12CFF7EF97BFE43F91B" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1A3036F8CC08C12CFF7EF97BFE43F91B" blockId="10.[151,1437,1332,1784]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFF7EF97BFECBF949" bold="true" box="[197,323,1680,1706]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7E1E4B09CC08C12CFEF7F97AFDD5F948" author="Hampson" box="[332,605,1681,1707]" pageId="10" pageNumber="52" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. Supplement. Volume I. Trustees of the British Museum, London, XXVIII + 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">
Hampson (
<number id="AC4724DFCC08C12CFE6FF97AFD9FF948" box="[468,535,1681,1707]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="1914.0">1914</number>
: 
<number id="AC4724DFCC08C12CFD9FF97AFDDCF948" box="[548,596,1681,1707]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="767.0">767</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized this species with 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFC51F97AFB3FF949" box="[1002,1207,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliterata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFC51F97AFB3FF949" box="[1002,1207,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Asura obliterata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<bibRefCitation id="7E1E4B09CC08C12CFB4BF97AFA15F948" author="Kuhne" box="[1264,1437,1681,1707]" pageId="10" pageNumber="52" refString="Kuhne, L. (2005) Neue taxa und neue synonyme afrikanischer Arctiidae (Lepidoptera). Lambillionea, CV, 3, 486 - 493." type="journal article" year="2005">
Kühne (
<number id="AC4724DFCC08C12CFAE8F97AFA1CF948" box="[1363,1428,1681,1707]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFE9BF953FE19F932" box="[288,401,1720,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFE9BF953FE19F932" box="[288,401,1720,1745]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">crenulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be valid. Examination of the male genitalia demonstrates 
<taxonomicName id="DD8F4D7BCC08C12CFBD7F953FB55F932" box="[1132,1245,1720,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenulata">
<emphasis id="28FBEAEACC08C12CFBD7F953FB55F932" box="[1132,1245,1720,1745]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">crenulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from other species in the genus.
</paragraph>
